                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13230642" author="stack" created="Thu, 15 Mar 2012 22:28:19 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks Eli for looking out for us.  Could do this in 0.96.  0.96 is going to be the big hbase singularity where we take on ugly, needed change.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This will be 0.24 hadoop (or cdh4)?  We&apos;ll need to add a shim to figure what the underlying hadoop supplies?  (We expect 0.96 to run on hadoop&apos;s as old as 1.0.x)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13230760" author="eli2" created="Fri, 16 Mar 2012 00:28:28 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Depends on you guys, and the Hadoop jira. I&apos;m happy to leave in the code (which will be dead code in Hadoop) in 23/cdh4 if that makes maintaining compatibility much easier for you. You guys could also insulate yourselves by copying the relevant methods into your branches if you want. I&apos;d be curious to know if you guys have people using this feature.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13230765" author="stack" created="Fri, 16 Mar 2012 00:31:24 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I think this feature was mentioned once inside my earshot that I remember.  I doubt it a widely used feature if its used at all.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Do others have an opinion on this?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13245389" author="stack" created="Tue, 3 Apr 2012 15:15:53 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Good candidate for the singularity release.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
